# Evan Chen style for LaTeX → PDF solutions

When producing a **full compilable** solution (not bare snippets), use this template so format, colours, and headers match **Evan Chen’s `evan.sty`** and the project’s reference pattern.

## Preamble

- `\documentclass[11pt]{scrartcl}`
- `\usepackage[sexy]{evan}` — requires **`evan.sty`** on `TEXINPUTS` or beside the `.tex` file (`[sexy]` = mdframed theorem boxes, purple section marks, long-doc layout).
- Set `\title{...}`, **`\author{...}`** (override package default author), optional `\date{\today}`, then `\maketitle`.

## Problem statement box

Wrap the statement in the purple framed style:

```latex
\begin{mdframed}[style=mdpurplebox,frametitle={Problem Statement}]
  % statement here
\end{mdframed}
```

## Body

- Structure main arguments with `\begin{claim}...\end{claim}` and `\begin{proof}...\end{proof}` (and other `evan` theorem envs as needed).
- Prefer `\soln` / `proof` naming consistent with the source problem.

## Headers and colour (do not fight defaults)

With KOMA + `evan` defaults, page headers use **inner: bold author — date**, **outer: bold title**, centred page number. Keep `[sexy]` unless the user asks otherwise; that drives **purple** section formatting and **green** claim boxes, **purple/violet** problem frame, and **hyperref** link colours from `evan.sty`.

